The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, February 09, 2004  Calcutta Column
 
	A special compartment should be allotted for vendors in  local trains, who are a menace on the Tarakeswar-Howrah  route. They block the narrow passage between the rows of  seats with huge baskets of vegetables and fruits, scarcely  leaving any space for passengers to move.  
	B.N. Bose, Dum Dum.  
	The riverbank off the Nimtala burning ghat is an eyesore.  Several unauthorised structures and shops have come up in  the area, which turns into a den of criminals after dark.  The ghat deserves better care, as it is where Tagore was  cremated. 
	 Anil Kumar Sen, Address not given. 

